ain language and accessible to nonspecialists in the history of Jewish law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJewish lawxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aJudaismxHistoryyTo 70 A.D. 0aQumran community. 0aRabbinical literaturexHistory and criticism. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh  a19th century.  a4qmmt.  acomprehensive study.  aconservative religion.  acultural studies.  adead sea scrolls.  ahalakhah.  ajewish history.  ajewish law.  ajewish practice.  ajewish scholars.  ajewish studies.  ajudaism.  alegal literature.  alegal material.  anonfiction.  apharisaic.  apolemical letter.  aqumran.  arabbinic judaism.  arabbinic law.  arabbis.  areligious history.  areligious law.  areligious scholars.  areligious scholarship.  asadducees.  asecond temple.  asectarians.1 aShemesh, Aharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094503640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520945036423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520945036/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles